.TH hsh 1 "August 2023" "1.0" "Simple Shell User Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh - Simple Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
hsh [options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The hsh (simple shell) is a command-line interface that interacts with a Linux operating system. It reads and executes commands entered by the user. It can interpret commands from either a file or the terminal. The hsh provides features for interactive use as well as non-interactive use through shell scripts.

.SH OPTIONS
The hsh command supports the following options:

.B -h, --help
Display a help message and exit.

.SH USAGE
The hsh command is used as follows:

$ hsh [options] [file]

.SH COMMANDS
The hsh supports various shell commands such as ls, pwd, cd, and more. It also allows users to execute external programs using their absolute or relative paths.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The hsh command returns the following exit status values:

0: Successful execution.
Other numbers: Indicates an error or failure.

.SH PATH
The hsh command searches for executable files in the directories listed in the PATH environment variable.

.SH EXAMPLES
To list files in the current directory:

$ hsh
$ ls

To change the working directory:

$ hsh
$ cd /path/to/directory

.SH BUGS
Single spaces are required after arguments.

